The changes address a SQL syntax error when using PgVectorStore with schema names containing hyphens. The fix involves quoting schema and table names with double quotes in SQL generation, updating the schema creation DDL, enhancing the schema validator to allow hyphenated names while preventing SQL injection, and improving error messages.

The `PgVectorSchemaValidator` now includes more robust checks against potential SQL injection vulnerabilities, rejecting names containing semicolons, comments, null bytes, newlines, carriage returns, and SQL keywords. The validation logic has been simplified and the error messages improved.

The `PgVectorStore`'s `getFullyQualifiedTableName` method now correctly quotes the schema and table names.

A new test case, `PgVectorStoreSchemaQuotingTest`, has been added to verify the correct quoting of hyphenated schema names in both SQL generation and similarity search.

The changes appear well-considered and address the reported issue effectively. The added test coverage is a good practice.

Approve.
